@@TJvImageSquare
<TITLEIMG TJvImageSquare>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Graphics.Shape
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A control that can display an image from an imagelist.
Description
  Use TJvImageSquare when you need a control that can display an image from an imagelist. By setting the
  Images and ImageIndex properties, the control displays the selected image in it's client area.

  Use properties like Color, HiColor and BorderStyle to modify the control's appearance. Use ShowClick
  to alter it's behavior.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageSquare.BorderStyle
Summary
  Specifies whether the control has a border.
Description
  Use BorderStyle to get or set whether the control has a border.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageSquare.HiColor
Summary
  Specifies the background color to use when hot tracking.
Description
  Use HiColor to specify the color to use when the mouse is hovering over the control.
See Also
  Color
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageSquare.ImageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the index of the image to display from the image list.
Description
  Use ImageIndex to specify the image to display in the control. The icon with
  the specified index is drawn using Images. To not display an image, set ImageIndex to -1.
See Also
  Images
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageSquare.Images
Summary
  Specifies an imagelist to retrieve the displayed image from.
Description
  Set Images to an imagelist where the component should retrieve the image to display. Images
  in combination with the ImageIndex property determines what image to display.
See Also
  ImageIndex
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageSquare.OnMouseEnter
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves over the control.
Description
  \Write an OnMouseEnter event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse over the
  control.
See Also
  OnMouseLeave
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageSquare.OnMouseLeave
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves off the control.
Description
  \Write an OnMouseLeave event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse off the
  control. For example, you can use this event to undo changes that were made in an OnMouseEnter
  event handler.
See Also
  OnMouseEnter
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageSquare.ShowClick
Summary
  Specifies if mouse clicks are shown visually.
Description
  Use ShowClick to specify whether mouse clinks are shown or not. if ShowClick is true, a small,
  double-line frame with a white background is drawn around the image when the user clicks with
  the mouse.
See Also
  Click, OnClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
