----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.AutoSize
Summary
  Specifies whether the control sizes itself automatically to accommodate its contents.
Description
  Use AutoSize to specify whether the control sizes itself automatically. When AutoSize is true,
  the control resizes automatically when its contents change.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.BackColor
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the control.
Description
  Use Color to read or change the background color of the control.
See Also
  FrontColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.ColCount
Summary
  Specifies the number of columns in the grid.
Description
  Use ColCount to specify how many columns the grid should display. When Optimal is set to true, ColCount
  might change.
See Also
  Optimal
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.FrontColor
Summary
  Specifies the color of the control's border.
Description
  Use FrontColor to specify a color to use for the control's border. FrontColor is also used to
  highlight the grid frame when ShowFrame is true,
See Also
  BackColor, ShowFrame
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.Ghost
Summary
  Specifies if the grid lines are "ghosted".
Description
  Use Ghost to specify if the grid lines in the control are ghosted, i.e if an extra border is drawn
  around the grid lines. The extra border is drawn using FrontColor.
See Also
  GridColor, FrontColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.GridColor
Summary
  Specifies the color used for the grid lines.
Description
  Use GridColor to set the color for the separator lines in the grid.
See Also
  Ghost, FrontColor, BackColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.ImageCount
Summary
  Specifies the number of images to display.
Description
  Use ImageCount to specify the number of images to display from Images. For example, setting
  ImageCount to 2, will only display the first 2 images in the imagelist. ImageCount can never be set
  to a value higher than Images.Count.
See Also
  ImageIndex, Images
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.ImageIndex
Summary
  Specifies the currently selected or clicked image.
Description
  \Read ImageIndex to determine which image is currently selected or clicked. If no image is selected,
  ImageIndex returns -1.
See Also
  Images
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.Images
Summary
  Specifies the images to display in the grid.
Description
  Set Images to the imagelist that should be displayed in the grid. If no imagelist is
  assigned, no images are displayed.
See Also
  ImageIndex, ColCount, ImageCount
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.Margin
Summary
  Specifies a margin to reserve around images.
Description
  Use Margin to set the number of pixels that surrounds each image. Setting Margin alters the size
  of each grid square.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.Optimal
Summary
  Specifies how the grid columns and rows are calculated.
Description
  Use Optimal to specify how rows and columns are calculated. If Optimal is true, the component
  alters the row and column count so that the grid occupies as little space as possible.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.SaveImage
Summary
  Saves an image in the imagelist to a file.
Description
  Call SaveImage to save an image from the imagelist to file.
Parameters
  Index    - Index of the image in the imagelist.
  Filename - The name of the file to save to. If Filename exists, it is overwritten.
  AsBmp    - Specifies if the image is saved as a bitmap or an icon. If true, the file is a bitmap file.
See Also
  SaveImageList
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.SaveImageList
Summary
  Saves the images in the imagelist to a composite bitmap file.
Description
  Call SaveImageList to save the content of Images to a bitmap file. The images in Images are
  merged into a single strip of images before saving to file.
Parameters
  Filename - The name of the file to save to. If Filename exists, it is overwritten.
See Also
  SaveImage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.ShowFrame
Summary
  Specifies whether the frame around images are hot tracked.
Description
  Set ShowFrame to true to make the control highlight the frame around the selected image when the
  mouse hovers over it. The highlight is drawn using FrontColor. Don't set ShowFrame to true unless
  ShowGrid is also true as doing so will leave frame traces when the user moves the mouse
  over the control.
See Also
  FrontColor, ShowGrid
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvImageWindow.ShowGrid
Summary
  Specifies if grid lines are shown.
Description
  Use ShowGrid to specify whether the control draws the horizontal and vertical grid lines. If ShowGrid
  is true, no grid is drawn. If ShowFrame is true, ShowGrid should also be true. The grid is drawn using
  GridColor.
See Also
  GridColor, ShowGrid, FrontColor, BackColor

